itunesNotes.standard: We love finding and pinning creative ideas, tasty recipes, and more. Pinterest’s wonderfully designed app is a constant source of inspiration, whether you’re planning a trip, remodeling your home, or finding something to wear. With a bevy of helpful features—from collaborative boards to built-in messaging—Pinterest is an exceptionally visual way to explore what matters to you.
itunesNotes.short: Get creative with your holiday decor.

itunesNotes.standard: More than just a dating app, Tinder has been updated to become one of the most engaging, fun, and social apps around. Of course, finding matches is still a huge highlight—but with smart group chats, an awesome Apple TV app, and Super Likes to go around, we’re swiping right on this one.
itunesNotes.short: Get faster matches with Tinder Platinum’s extra features.

itunesNotes.standard: Matchmaking app Bumble flips traditional social norms. Here, women make the first move. Some 50 million people have used it to not only find a date but also make friends and conduct business. If you don’t start chatting within 24 hours, the match disappears—encouraging you to actually talk to people.
itunesNotes.short: Find love, friendship, or professional connections.

itunesNotes.standard: Your houseplants will love this app. Simply tell Planta a location (living room, kitchen, office) and how much light the area gets and the app will recommend the plants most likely to survive there. Maybe a pothos for shady spots, a moth orchid for sunnier ones. With Planta, you can turn your home into a horticultural haven.
